Triggers bundled by Aliases yield weighted Replies
The term Alias might need a rename, but it is what it is for now.

Alias has a Rate in (0..1] that defaults to 1
Can be overridden by trigger rate, if it is set

Triggers:
Regex --> Substring is implied unless properly indicated.
    - FUTURE: Logical operators and slightly more complicated operands (like message author permissions)?
Triggers have optional rate in (0..1] that overrides alias / bucket rate

Replies:
PISS-compatible string. Has a weight [1..256] (todo: internally decrement by 1 to use exactly 8 bits, and make a weight of 0 incompatible.)
Weights relate relative picking chance: reply A with weight 256 is picked 256x as often as reply B with weight 1 and 128x as often as reply C with weight 2

As such, as is required:

Alias:
- Name (unique, for editing triggers / replies purposes)
- ID (internal only, keeps things held together after Alias rename)

Trigger:
- Type (Purely for future compatibility)
- Data (String output)
- ? Rate (optional override rate, [1..256]
- BucketID (ID of attached Alias)
- ID (increasing unique number for ordering reasons)

Reply:
- Data (PISS-compatible string output)
- Weight
- BucketID
- ID (increasing unique number for ordering reasons)

Implementation:
Everything stored in separate tables (BUCKET, TRIGGER, REPLY)
Keep triggers in memory in a cache -> Prevent repeatedly fetching from db, keeping db as a disk-based storage medium for startup and long-term storage reasons.
